50|$|Silvaco Data Systems v. Intel Corp was a {{trade secrets}} case heard before the California Court of Appeal for the Sixth District. Silvaco sued Intel for {{misappropriation}} of trade secrets because Intel used software {{produced by a}} third-party that had misappropriated Silvaco's trade secrets. The appeals court affirmed {{the decision of the}} trial court <b>to</b> <b>grant</b> summary <b>judgment</b> in favor of Intel, finding that merely using infringing software does not constitute a trade secret infringement in itself.|$|R
