50|$|Varnum v. Brien, 763 N.W.2d 862 (Iowa 2009), was a {{unanimous}} {{decision of the}} Iowa Supreme Court dated April 3, 2009, that held the state's limitation of marriage to opposite-sex couples violated the equal protection clause of the Iowa Constitution. It established same-sex marriage in Iowa. In 2007, a lower court had <b>granted</b> summary <b>judgment</b> in favor of six same-sex couples who sued Timothy Brien, Polk County Recorder, for refusing <b>to</b> <b>grant</b> them marriage licenses.|$|R
